"title": "5214: attack",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5214: attack",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A violent act of aggression often associated with intent to invade, sometimes as an act of retribution and occasionally as a strategic act of self-defence. Scripture also recognises the possibility of spiritual aggression through attack by evil forces.</p>\n<h2>Examples of God's people attacking others</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:14-Gen14:16\">GEN 14:14–14:16</a> <em>Abraham attacks the captors of the king of Sodom</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:19-Judg7:21\">JDG 7:19–7:21</a> <em>Gideon attacks the Midianites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:13-1Sam14:14\">1SA 14:13–14:14</a> <em>Jonathan attacks the Philistines</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:6-2Sam5:7\">2SA 5:6–5:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:4-1Chr11:5\">1CH 11:4–11:5</a> <em>David attacks the Jebusites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:1-Deut20:20\">DEU 20:1–20:20</a> <em>Moses gives detailed instruction on going to war.</em></p>\n<h3>The Israelites attack the inhabitants of Canaan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:2\">JOS 6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:20\">JOS 6:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:1-Josh8:3\">JOS 8:1–8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:21-Josh8:22\">JOS 8:21–8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:9-Josh10:10\">JOS 10:9–10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:29-Josh10:42\">JOS 10:29–10:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:7-Josh11:8\">JOS 11:7–11:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:16-Josh11:23\">JOS 11:16–11:23</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of God's people attacked by others</h2>\n<h3>By the Amalekites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:8-Exod17:13\">EXO 17:8–17:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>By the Midianites</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:1-Judg6:6\">JDG 6:1–6:6</a></p>\n<h3>By the Ammonites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:9\">JDG 10:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:4-Judg11:6\">JDG 11:4–11:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:8\">2SA 10:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:9\">1CH 19:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:1\">2CH 20:1</a></p>\n<h3>By the Philistines</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:7\">1SA 7:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:17\">2SA 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:22\">2SA 5:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr14:8\">1CH 14:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr14:13\">1CH 14:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:1-Ps56:2\">PSA 56:1–56:2</a></p>\n<h3>By Syria (Aram)</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:1\">1KI 20:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:26\">1KI 20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:21-2Kgs3:27\">2KI 3:21–3:27</a> <em>the Moabites seek to attack Israel but are routed</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:2\">2KI 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:24-2Kgs6:25\">2KI 6:24–6:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:17\">2KI 12:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:1-2Chr16:4\">2CH 16:1–16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:5\">2CH 28:5</a></p>\n<h3>By the Egyptians</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:1-2Chr12:4\">2CH 12:1–12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:7-2Chr12:9\">2CH 12:7–12:9</a></p>\n<h2>Attacks on God's people resulting in exile</h2>\n<h3>Israel attacked by the Assyrians</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:3-2Kgs17:6\">2KI 17:3–17:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:9-2Kgs18:12\">2KI 18:9–18:12</a></p>\n<h3>Judah attacked by the Babylonians</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:5-2Chr36:7\">2CH 36:5–36:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:1\">2KI 24:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:10-2Kgs24:16\">2KI 24:10–24:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:1\">2KI 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:8-2Kgs25:11\">2KI 25:8–25:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15-2Chr36:20\">2CH 36:15–36:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:24\">JER 32:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:21\">EZK 33:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's people attack each other</h2>\n<h3>Intertribal warfare</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:22-Judg9:23\">JDG 9:22–9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:39-Judg9:45\">JDG 9:39–9:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:18-Judg20:48\">JDG 20:18–20:48</a></p>\n<h3>The north (Israel) and south (Judah) attack each other</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:11-2Kgs14:14\">2KI 14:11–14:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:20-2Chr25:24\">2CH 25:20–25:24</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:1-2Chr13:3\">2CH 13:1–13:3</a></p>\n<h3>Attacks within the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:1-Jas4:2\">JAS 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:2\">PHP 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:15\">1TH 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:11-Jas4:12\">JAS 4:11–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:9\">1PE 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of individuals who were attacked</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:8\">GEN 4:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:22\">ACT 16:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:12-Exod21:20\">EXO 21:12–21:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:9-1Sam19:10\">1SA 19:9–19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:7\">1SA 24:7</a></p>\n<h2>The danger of attack by Satan and his agents</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:8-1Pet5:9\">1PE 5:8–5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">MAT 4:1–4:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:12\">EPH 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:7\">REV 11:7</a></p>\n<h2>God provides protection against both physical and spiritual attack</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:13-Eph6:18\">EPH 6:13–6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:10\">PSA 7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:1-Ps18:3\">PSA 18:1–18:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps138:7\">PSA 138:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:18\">2TI 4:18</a></p>",
